  "prompt": "Which one is better for economy, demand deposit or time deposit?",
  "response": "Both demand deposits and time deposits have their advantages and can serve different economic purposes:\n\nDemand Deposits:\n1. Provides high liquidity\n2. Easy to access funds immediately\n3. Lower interest rates\n4. Useful for daily transactions\n5. Supports economic flexibility\n\nTime Deposits:\n1. Higher interest rates\n2. Encourages saving\n3. Provides banks with stable funds for lending\n4. Helps banks support economic investments\n5. Less liquid, with penalties for early withdrawal\n\nFrom an overall economic perspective, a balanced mix of both is generally considered beneficial:\n- Demand deposits support day-to-day economic activities\n- Time deposits promote savings and provide capital for investments\n\nThe \"better\" option depends on specific economic goals and individual financial needs. Neither is universally superior; they serve complementary functions in the economic system.",
